","workspace_file_chunks":[]},{"status":"success","request_id":"5f0b5c04-7891-47ec-9896-3c55ed33a3c7","request_message":"","structured_output_nodes":[{"id":1,"type":5,"content":"","tool_use":{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Q67H1QgifGd9PjVt4MDCo8","tool_name":"str-replace-editor","input_json":"{"command": "str_replace", "path": "src/main/java/com/omdmrotat/rtpportal/PortalRTPTask.java", "instruction_reminder": "ALWAYS BREAK DOWN EDITS INTO SMALLER CHUNKS OF AT MOST 150 LINES EACH.", "old_str_1": " @Override\n public void run() {\n if (plugin.getPlayersInPortal().isEmpty()) {\n plugin.getTeleportTimer().set(plugin.getConfigManager().getTeleportTimer());\n return;\n }\n\n int currentTime = plugin.getTeleportTimer().get();\n\n\n for (UUID playerUUID : plugin.getPlayersInPortal()) {\n Player player = Bukkit.getPlayer(playerUUID);\n if (player != null) {\n sendCountdownTitle(player, currentTime);\n }\n }\n\n if (currentTime == 0) {\n // Filter out players who are in combat before teleporting\n Set<UUID> playersToTeleport = plugin.getCombatLogXIntegration()\n .filterPlayersNotInCombat(plugin.getPlayersInPortal());\n\n if (!playersToTeleport.isEmpty()) {\n plugin.getTeleportManager().findAndTeleportPlayers(playersToTeleport);\n } else {\n plugin.getLogger().info(\"No players could be teleported - all players are either offline or in combat.\");\n }\n }\n\n if (plugin.getTeleportTimer().decrementAndGet() < 0) {\n plugin.getTeleportTimer().set(plugin.getConfigManager().getTeleportTimer());\n }\n }", "new_str_1": " @Override\n public void run() {\n // Clean up offline players and players who are no longer in the region\n cleanupPlayersInPortal();\n \n if (plugin.getPlayersInPortal().isEmpty()) {\n plugin.getTeleportTimer().set(plugin.getConfigManager().getTeleportTimer());\n return;\n }\n\n int currentTime = plugin.getTeleportTimer().get();\n\n // Send countdown titles only to players who are actually in the portal region\n for (UUID playerUUID : new HashSet<>(plugin.getPlayersInPortal())) {\n Player player = Bukkit.getPlayer(playerUUID);\n if (player != null && isPlayerInPortalRegion(player)) {\n sendCountdownTitle(player, currentTime);\n }\n }\n\n if (currentTime == 0) {\n // Filter out players who are in combat before teleporting\n Set<UUID> playersToTeleport = plugin.getCombatLogXIntegration()\n .filterPlayersNotInCombat(plugin.getPlayersInPortal());\n\n if (!playersToTeleport.isEmpty()) {\n plugin.getTeleportManager().findAndTeleportPlayers(playersToTeleport);\n } else {\n plugin.getLogger().info(\"No players could be teleported - all players are either offline or in combat.\");\n }\n }\n\n if (plugin.getTeleportTimer().decrementAndGet() < 0) {\n plugin.getTeleportTimer().set(plugin.getConfigManager().getTeleportTimer());\n }\n }", "old_str_start_line_number_1": 22, "old_str_end_line_number_1": 54}","mcp_server_name":"","mcp_tool_name":""}},{"id":2,"type":0,"content":"I found the issue! The problem is in the logic flow. Here's what's happening:

1. **Players enter the portal** → Added to `playersInPortal` set
2. **Timer counts down** → All players in the set see the countdown
3. **Timer hits 0** → Players in combat are filtered out but **remain in the `playersInPortal` set**
4. **Timer resets** → The cycle continues with the same players still in the set
5. **Players who left the region** → The `WorldGuardRegionListener` correctly removes them, but there might be edge cases

The main issue is that the current logic doesn't properly handle the case where players want to leave the portal but are stuck in the countdown cycle. Let me fix this by improving the region detection and adding better cleanup logic:
