 \n \" (max allowed: \" + String.format(\"%.1f%%\", maxWaterPercentage * 100) + \")\");\n return false;\n }\n \n // Check for water above if enabled (prevents underwater caves)\n if (config.isCheckWaterAbove()) {\n int checkHeight = config.getCheckAboveHeight();\n for (int dy = 1; dy <= checkHeight; dy++) {\n Block blockAbove = world.getBlockAt(x, y + dy, z);\n if (isWaterBlock(blockAbove.getType())) {\n plugin.getLogger().info(\"Rejected location at \" + x + \",\" + y + \",\" + z + \n \" - water detected \" + dy + \" blocks above\");\n return false;\n }\n }\n }\n \n return true;\n }\n \n /**\n * Checks if a material is a water block (including waterlogged blocks).\n * @param material The material to check\n * @return true if the material is water-related\n */\n private boolean isWaterBlock(Material material) {\n return material == Material.WATER || \n material == Material.KELP || \n material == Material.KELP_PLANT ||\n material == Material.SEAGRASS ||\n material == Material.TALL_SEAGRASS ||\n material == Material.SEA_PICKLE ||\n material.name().contains(\"CORAL\") ||\n material.name().contains(\"WATERLOGGED\");\n }\n\n private void teleportPlayersToLocation(Set<UUID> players, Location location) {", "old_str_start_line_number_1": 97, "old_str_end_line_number_1": 99}","mcp_server_name":"","mcp_tool_name":""}},{"id":2,"type":0,"content":"Now let me add the water detection method to the TeleportManager:
