### **Version-Safe Approach:**

```java
// Core ocean biomes (exist in all versions)
oceanBiomes.add(Biome.OCEAN);
oceanBiomes.add(Biome.DEEP_OCEAN);

// Version-specific biomes (safely added if they exist)
addBiomeIfExists("WARM_OCEAN");
addBiomeIfExists("DEEP_WARM_OCEAN"); // Won't crash if missing
```

### ️ **Error Handling:**

The `addBiomeIfExists()` method safely handles missing biomes:
- **If biome exists**: Adds it to the ocean biomes set
- **If biome missing**: Logs info message and continues
- **No crashes**: Plugin continues working regardless of Minecraft version

### **Logging:**

The system now provides helpful feedback:
- `"Initialized 8 ocean biomes for detection"` (success message)
- `"Biome DEEP_WARM_OCEAN not available in this version, skipping"` (version info)

### **Benefits:**

1. **Cross-Version Compatibility**: Works on older and newer Minecraft versions
2. **No Compilation Errors**: No more "Cannot resolve symbol" errors
3. **Graceful Degradation**: Missing biomes don't break the plugin
4. **Future-Proof**: New ocean biomes can be easily added

This approach ensures the plugin will work across different Minecraft versions without compilation errors or runtime crashes!
